name: Einstein
description:
Black and White Acrylic, Fabric and Regular Matte Gel on a 24”x30” Canvas

I painted the “Mug Shot” collection to embody the contrasting  sides of a genius mind. Einstein was the inspiration for this collection being one of the most influential scientists in history. On August 8th, 1939 Albert Einstein wrote to President Roosevelt warning about the possibility of an Atomic Bomb using Uranium.

painted by kaytlyne dewald

name: Karl Marx Mug Shot
description:
Black and White Acrylic, Fabric and Regular Matte Gel on a 24”x30” Canvas

I painted the “Mug Shot” collection to embody the contrasting  sides of a genius mind. Einstein was the inspiration for this collection being one of the most influential scientists in history. Karl Marx was a German philosopher who developed the socio-political theory of Marxism. His theories played a significant role during the development of social science and the socialist political movement.

painted by kaytlyne dewald

name: Warhol
description:
Black and White Acrylic, Fabric 
and Regular Matte Gel on a 24”x30” Canvas

I painted the “Mug Shot” collection to embody the contrasting  sides of a genius mind and how alot of genius were reduced to criminals and not appreciated as they are today. Andy Warhol was the leading figure in pop art. In 1963 he painted 8 Elvises which sold for $100 million on Nov.26th 2009.

painted by kaytlyne dewald

name: Camel
description:
Black, white and saffron Acrylic Paint, Fabric and Regular Matte Gel on a 24" x 30" Canvas

In India the Camel is a symbol of Love, because if you can love a camel you can love anything. This Camel is “kirschner”, I rode him in Pushkar, India into the desert for an amazing night eating curry over a fire, drinking and dancing with gypsies.

painted by kaytlyne dewald
